cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CV 

This paper discusses the use of semi-supervised classification for natural language processing tasks such as parsing, biomedical information processing, text classification, and summarization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the performance of semi-supervised classification, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions text classification and summarization, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) respectively.
